  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "The Urdesh campaign reaches its climax inside the city of Eltath, where Warmaster Macaroth's headquarters has become the target of an in-person decapitation push by Anarch Sek himself. Sek arrives on the planet to take the Warmaster's life, breaking every rule of Archenemy command doctrine and forcing the Crusade leadership into a desperate close-quarters defence of the command palaces and tactical-control nodes. The Tanith First fights through the urban-warfare maze of Eltath in fragments — Rawne running one column, Hark another, Daur and Criid coordinating the Mkoll-led scout teams — converging slowly on the Macaroth-Sek confrontation. The Felyx Chass subplot, the long-running Yoncy Kolea daemon-whisper subplot, and the Sirkle internal-conspiracy thread all close out, costing the regiment several of its longest-serving figures. Series climax. Closes with Sek killed, the Crusade strategic balance permanently tipped, and the Tanith First reduced again to a smaller, harder unit.",
